attributes.name: instanceId
attributes.description: Internal identifier of the nasServer instance.

attributes.name: id
attributes.description: Unique identifier of the nasServer instance.

attributes.name: objectId
attributes.description: Unique backend or internal ID of the nasServer object

attributes.name: name
attributes.description: User-specified name of the NAS server.

attributes.name: health
attributes.description: Health information for the NAS server, as defined by the health resource type.

attributes.name: homeSP
attributes.description: Storage Processor on which the NAS Server is intended to run.

attributes.name: currentSP
attributes.description: Storage Processor on which the NAS server is currently running.

attributes.name: pool
attributes.description: Storage pool that stores the NAS server's configuration metadata, as defined by the pool resource type.

attributes.name: sizeAllocated
attributes.description: Amount of storage pool space used for NAS server configuration.

attributes.name: isSystem
attributes.description:
Indicates whether the NAS server is a system NAS server. Value are:
  • true - NAS server is a system NAS server.
  • false - NAS server is not a system NAS server.

attributes.name: isReplicationEnabled
attributes.description:
Indicates whether a replication session is enabled for the NAS server. The NAS server can't be deleted while replication session is enabled. Values are:
  • true - Replication session is enabled.
  • false - Replication session is disabled.

attributes.name: isReplicationDestination
attributes.description:
Indicates whether the NAS server is a replication destination. Values are:
  • true - NAS server is a replication destination.
  • false - NAS server is a not a replication destination.

attributes.name: replicationType
attributes.description: Replication type.

attributes.name: type
attributes.description: NAS server type.

attributes.name: defaultUnixUser
attributes.description: Default Unix user name to use for an unmapped Windows user. This value only applies when the value of allowUnmappedUser is true.

attributes.name: defaultWindowsUser
attributes.description: Default Windows user name to use for an unmapped Unix user. This value only applies when the value of allowUnmappedUser is true.

attributes.name: currentUnixDirectoryService
attributes.description: Unix Directory Service used to look up users and hosts.

attributes.name: isMultiProtocolEnabled
attributes.description:
Indicates whether multiprotocol sharing mode is enabled. This mode enables simultaneous file access for Windows and Unix users. Values are:
  • true - Multiprotocol sharing mode is enabled.
  • false - Multiprotocol sharing mode is disabled.

attributes.name: isWindowsToUnixUsernameMappingEnabled
attributes.description:
Indicates whether a Unix to/from Windows user name mapping is enabled. Values are:
  • true - Unix to/from Windows user name mapping is enabled.
  • false - Unix to/from Windows user name mapping is disabled.

attributes.name: credentialsCacheTTL
attributes.description: DEPRECATED. The similar property was added to NFS server. Time-To-Live expiration stamp for a Windows entry in the credentials cache. When failed mapping entries expire, the system retries mapping the UID to the SID.

attributes.name: isExtendedUnixCredentialEnabled
attributes.description:
DEPRECATED. The similar property was added to NFS server. Indicates whether more than 16 Unix groups are supported in a Unix credential. Values are:
  • true - NAS server supports more than 16 Unix groups in a Unix credential.
  • false - NAS server does not support more than 16 Unix groups in a Unix credential.

attributes.name: allowUnmappedUser
attributes.description:
Indicates whether an unmappped user can access the NAS server as a default user. Values are:
  • true - Allow access for unmapped users.
  • false - Disallow access for unmapped users.

attributes.name: cifsServer
attributes.description: The cifsServers associated with the current nasServer

attributes.name: fileDNSServer
attributes.description: The fileDNSServer associated with the current nasServer

attributes.name: fileInterface
attributes.description: The fileInterfaces associated with the current nasServer

attributes.name: preferredInterfaceSettings
attributes.description: The preferredInterfaceSettings associated with the current nasServer

attributes.name: virusChecker
attributes.description: The virusChecker associated with the current nasServer
